	 <title>System.ToBoolean</title> 
	 <para></para> 
	 <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Remarks</bridgehead> 
	 <para> <symbol>Byte</symbol>, <symbol>Integer</symbol>,
		  <symbol>Long</symbol>, <symbol>Short</symbol>, and <symbol>String</symbol>
		  types can be explicitly converted to <symbol>Boolean</symbol> using this
		  operator.</para> 
	 <para>With a numeric value, 0 will return as <symbol>false</symbol>, any
		  other value will return as <symbol>true</symbol>.</para> 
	 <para>With strings, a case-insensative compare is done. The string "true"
		  will return true, the string "false" will return false. An error will occur if
		  the string is not one of the two.</para> 
	 <para>An error will occur if the value is outside that range of an
		  <symbol>Short</symbol> (-32768 to +32767).</para> 
	 <example> 
		  <title>Example</title> 
		  <programlisting>select ToBoolean(-1234);
select ToBoolean("fALsE");</programlisting> 
		  <programlisting>True
False</programlisting> 
	 </example> 
